window.I18N_ZH={"AI Engineering — Henry Lee": "AI 工程 — Henry Lee", "Home": "首页", "Work": "工作", "Lab": "实验室", "Notes": "笔记", "Contact": "联系", "ai engineering": "AI 工程", "Engineering": "工程", "Using AI well is an engineering discipline, not a habit. I built my team's AI delivery system — the pipeline, the gates, the context, the review roles — and it ships real features.": "用好 AI 是一门工程学科,不是一个习惯。我团队的 AI 交付体系是我搭的——pipeline、门禁、context、review 角色——它交付的是真实的功能。", "10 pipeline stages": "10 个 pipeline 阶段", "24 skills · 8.7k lines": "24 个 skills · 8.7k 行", "16 features shipped through it": "16 个功能经它上线", "30+ per-service context files": "32 份按服务的 context 文件", "4 role-based AI reviewers": "4 个按角色分工的 AI reviewer", "feature drafts: days → hours": "功能初稿:数天 → 数小时", "the failure file": "失败档案", "The failure": "失败", "file": "档案", "Every AI success story you'll read is missing this section. Here's what went wrong in ours — the discipline came from the failures.": "你读到的每一个 AI 成功故事,都缺了这一节。这是我们这套体系里出过的错——纪律正是从失败里长出来的。", "The fix that broke production": "把生产搞坏的那次修复", "The agent found a real bug — one that had sat harmless in production for years — and repaired it. The repair changed behavior other code had quietly grown to depend on, and things blew up. Lesson: an agent evaluates code; it doesn't know your system's history. A harmless bug is load-bearing until proven otherwise.": "agent 找到了一个真 bug——在生产上无害地躺了好几年——然后把它修了。这一修,改掉了其他代码早已悄悄依赖的行为,东西就炸了。教训:agent 评估的是代码,它不知道你系统的历史。一个无害的 bug,在证明之前都要当它是承重的。", "The big answer to a small ask": "小需求,大答案", "The requirement was genuinely small — an existing rule needed one more condition, a change the codebase was already shaped for. The agent, not grasping that intent, rebuilt the surrounding flow instead: hundreds of new lines that technically worked and doubled the review burden. Lesson: the smallest correct change comes from knowing what the codebase already wants to do — that judgment is still ours.": "需求真的很小——给一条现有规则多加一个条件,代码库本来就是为这种改动准备的。agent 没抓住这层意图,把周边的流程重建了一遍:几百行新代码,技术上能跑,review 负担翻倍。教训:最小的正确改动,来自知道代码库本来想怎么做——这个判断仍然在我们手上。", "Correct, and slow": "正确,但慢", "Asked for accuracy, the agent updated the database row by row — correct, and an IO storm at our volume. Batching was the obvious answer, but only obvious to someone who has paid for IO before. Lesson: performance instincts don't ship with the model; they come from the scars.": "要求它保证准确,agent 就一行一行地更新数据库——正确,但在我们的量级上是一场 IO 风暴。批量处理是显而易见的答案,可只对为 IO 付过学费的人显而易见。教训:性能直觉不随模型出厂,它来自伤疤。", "The pattern behind all three: the damage happens when someone can't yet tell a good answer from a plausible one — a junior burning tokens on the wrong question, merging changes they can't explain. So the rule is not \"use AI less.\" It is:": "三件事背后是同一个模式:当一个人还分不出「好答案」和「像样的答案」时,伤害就发生了——junior 在错误的问题上烧 token,merge 自己解释不了的改动。所以规则不是「少用 AI」,而是:", "discernment first, delegation second": "先有判断力,再谈委派", ". You must be able to judge the problem and the logic before you outsource the typing.": "。你得先能评判问题和逻辑,才能把打字外包出去。", "the delivery system": "交付体系", "The delivery": "交付", "system": "体系", "An artifact-gated, 10-stage delivery pipeline built as agent skills: requirements document (PRD) → design → contracts → SDK → tasks → parallel agent development → machine-judged acceptance. Every artifact carries a human approval signature, and irreversible actions — publish, push, migrations — require explicit human confirmation.": "一条以产物为门禁、10 个阶段的交付 pipeline,用 agent skills 搭起来:需求文档(PRD)→ 设计 → 契约 → SDK → 任务 → 多 agent 并行开发 → 机器判定验收。每份产物都带人工批准签名,不可逆的动作——publish、push、migration——必须由人明确确认。", "Artifact Pipeline": "产物 pipeline", "Role-based Review": "按角色 review", "Human Gates": "人工门禁", "Team-built AI incident diagnoser living in our team chat: symptoms in, trace-backed hypotheses out — reading production logs over MCP and code across every repo, frontend and backend. The real work was making the system diagnosable first: standardized errors, trace IDs through every hop, names that tell you what broke. The bot is the payoff; the discipline is the design.": "团队自建的 AI 事故诊断器,住在团队 chat 里:症状进,带 trace 佐证的假设出——通过 MCP 读生产日志,读遍每个仓库的代码,前端后端都在内。真正的功夫是先把系统变得可诊断:标准化的错误、贯穿每一跳的 trace ID、一看就知道坏在哪的命名。bot 是回报,纪律才是设计。", "Standardized Tracing": "标准化 tracing", "Event Schema Registry": "事件 Schema Registry", "JSON-Schema-first event contracts with multi-language SDK codegen (Node, Java, Rust) — producers and consumers can't drift because the schema is the source of truth.": "JSON-Schema 先行的事件契约,配多语言 SDK 代码生成(Node、Java、Rust)——schema 就是唯一事实来源,生产者和消费者想漂移也漂移不了。", "Codegen": "代码生成", "Multi-language SDK": "多语言 SDK", "Operations agent (human-in-the-loop)": "运营 agent(human-in-the-loop)", "A LangChain agent living in our team chat: operations asks in natural language, the agent resolves the target audience, shows a preview, and executes only after an explicit \"confirm\" — every step audit-logged. The same gate philosophy as everything else I build.": "一个住在团队 chat 里的 LangChain agent:运营用自然语言提需求,agent 解析出目标用户群,先给预览,收到明确的「confirm」才执行——每一步都留审计日志。和我做的其他东西,同一套门禁哲学。", "Preview-first": "预览先行", "Context engineering": "Context 工程", "Clever prompts don't scale; engineered context does — a routing manifest across 17 repositories, 30+ per-service context files, and persistent memory across sessions. The agent starts every task already knowing the codebase.": "巧妙的 prompt 撑不起规模,工程化的 context 才行——一份横跨 17 个仓库的路由清单、32 份按服务的 context 文件,加上跨 session 的持久记忆。agent 接到任何任务时,已经认识这套代码库了。", "Routing Manifest": "路由清单", "Context Files": "Context 文件", "Persistent Memory": "持久记忆", "working with agents": "与 agent 协作", "Principles of working with": "与 agent 协作的", "agents": "原则", "AI proposes, humans approve.": "AI 提议,人来批准。", "Every irreversible action — commit, publish, deploy, migration — sits behind an explicit human gate. No agent ever commits.": "每一个不可逆的动作——commit、publish、部署、migration——都在一道明确的人工门禁后面。任何 agent 都不许 commit。", "AI compresses the zero-to-eighty stretch.": "AI 压缩的是从零到八十的那段路。", "A two-day build becomes a two-hour first draft. The last twenty percent is still ours, and the real skill is discernment: catching what it got wrong.": "两天的活变成两小时的初稿。最后那百分之二十仍然归我们,真正的本事是判断力:抓出它做错的地方。", "AI amplifies your code culture.": "AI 放大你的代码文化。", "Rot in, rot out — an agent raised on a disciplined codebase ships discipline; raised on mess, it ships mess faster.": "喂进去什么,长出来什么——在有纪律的代码库里养大的 agent,交付纪律;在烂摊子里养大的,只会更快地交付烂摊子。", "Context beats prompts.": "Context 胜过 prompt。", "The agent should start every task already knowing the codebase — routing manifests, per-service context files, persistent memory — not a cleverly worded request.": "agent 接到任务时就该已经认识代码库——路由清单、按服务的 context 文件、持久记忆——而不是靠一句措辞巧妙的请求。", "Incidents compile into policy.": "事故要编译成规矩。", "A production lesson becomes a rule wired into the agent harness — a readiness gate the agent can't skip, so the same mistake can't ship twice.": "一次生产教训变成写进 agent harness 的规则——一道 agent 跳不过的就绪门禁,同一个错误就不可能上线第二次。", "the rules": "规矩", "The rules my agents": "我的 agent 要守的", "live by": "规矩", "Both of my agents — the one at work and the one at home — run under the same standing rules. Every one of them was written the hard way.": "我的两个 agent——公司那个和家里那个——跑在同一套长期规则下。每一条都是踩过坑才写下来的。", "Rule 0: no guessing.": "规则 0:不许猜。", "Verify before speaking; if you can't verify, say so.": "先验证再开口;验证不了,就直说验证不了。", "My words mean exactly what they say.": "我的话就是字面意思。", "Don't interpret, don't complete my thoughts — ask.": "不要解读,不要替我补完想法——问。", "Execute only what was asked.": "只执行被要求的事。", "\"While I'm here, let me also…\" is where incidents start.": "「顺手把这个也……」正是事故的起点。", "Show proof after every write.": "每次写入后都要给证据。", "\"Done\" is a claim; a file path is evidence.": "「做完了」是一句主张,文件路径才是证据。", "Discussion is not permission.": "讨论不等于许可。", "Talking about running something is not approval to run it.": "聊到要跑某个东西,不等于批准去跑。", "\"It ran\" is not \"it works.\"": "「跑过了」不等于「跑对了」。", "Verify after every execution.": "每次执行后都要验证。", "Slow is fine.": "慢不要紧,", "Wrong is not.": "错不行。", "raising an agent": "养 agent", "Raising an": "养一个", "The Lab page shows what my home agent does. This is how it got that way — the same method I use on the agents at work, run twice, converging on the same constitution.": "实验室那页展示的是我家里那个 agent 会做什么。这一页讲它是怎么长成这样的——和我在公司调教 agent 用的是同一套方法,跑了两遍,收敛出同一部宪法。", "Constitution before tasks": "先立宪法,再派活", "On day two of the agent's life I installed SOUL.md — its identity file: problem-solving protocol, naming rules, behavioral law — before it did any real work. Rules don't retrofit well.": "agent 出生的第二天,我就给它装上了 SOUL.md——它的身份文件:解题协议、命名规则、行为法——在它干任何正经活之前。规矩这种东西,事后补装是装不牢的。", "Small jobs first": "小活先行", "New agent, small scope. I watch where it stalls or overreaches, then widen. It's the same calibrated-challenge ladder I use on junior engineers.": "新 agent,只 delegate 小范围的活。我盯着它在哪儿卡壳、在哪儿越界,再逐步放宽。这和我带 junior 工程师用的,是同一把校准过难度的阶梯。", "Every failure becomes law, immediately": "失败即立法,当天生效", "It executed without confirmation three times in one session — that same day, \"discussion is not permission\" became permanent law. Six standing rules; every one has an incident behind it.": "一个 session 里,它三次没等确认就执行——当天,「讨论不等于许可」就成了永久法条。六条长期规则,每一条背后都有一次事故。", "Writes must show receipts": "写入要出示证据", "After every correction the agent must show the stored entry — ID and content. \"Got it\" is not evidence that learning happened.": "每次纠正之后,agent 必须把存进去的条目亮出来——ID 和内容。一句「记住了」,不能证明学习真的发生过。", "Memory has an economy": "记忆有经济学", "Every always-loaded fact costs tokens forever, so MEMORY.md — the always-loaded layer — has a 7-day admission test: still true and useful in a week, or it doesn't get in. Facts route by weight — behavioral law loads every turn, Mnemosyne holds the long tail for on-demand recall, transcripts stay searchable but out of the way.": "每一条常驻加载的事实都要永远付 token 成本,所以 MEMORY.md——常驻加载的那一层——设了「7 天准入测试」:一周后还真、还有用,才准进。事实按分量分流——行为法每一轮都加载,Mnemosyne 存放长尾、按需召回,聊天记录可搜索,但不占道。", "Tune the harness, not just the prompt": "连 harness 一起调,不只调 prompt", "The expensive model was over-serving simple execution, so it got demoted to deep-reasoning duty only. An update wiped the config once — pre-update backups went on that day. A nightly memory digest, a weekly consolidation pass, a monthly self-audit: the agent maintains itself, on a schedule.": "贵的模型被过度用在简单执行上,于是降级为只值 deep-reasoning 的班。一次更新抹掉过一回 config——当天就加上了更新前备份。每晚一份记忆 digest,每周一轮整合,每月一次自查:agent 按日程维护它自己。", "Two agents, two independent memory stores, one converging constitution. That's when you know it's a method — not a habit.": "两个 agent,两套独立记忆,收敛出同一部宪法——这时候你才知道,这是方法,不是习惯。", "the constraints": "约束", "Every tool answers a": "每个工具都在回答一个", "constraint": "约束", "None of this tooling exists because it's cool. Large language models have a handful of hard constraints — and every piece of my stack is a direct answer to one of them.": "这些工具没有一样是因为\"酷\"才存在的。大语言模型有几条绕不开的硬约束——我的每一件工具,都是对其中一条的直接回答。", "Context is finite": "上下文是有限的", "A model can only hold so much, so relevance beats volume: a routing manifest across 17 repositories decides where a task belongs, and 30+ per-service context files mean the agent starts already knowing the codebase — instead of re-reading it every session.": "模型装不下所有东西,所以\"相关\"比\"多\"重要:一份覆盖 17 个 repo 的路由清单决定任务归哪里,30+ 份 per-service context 文件让 agent 一开工就认识代码库——而不是每个 session 重新读一遍。", "Memory doesn't persist": "记忆不会自己留下", "The biggest handicap of any agent: session ends, knowledge gone. My answer is layered — an identity file for law, an always-loaded fact file with a 7-day admission test, a vector store (Mnemosyne, 3,700+ entries) for the long tail, and Obsidian as the human-curated layer on top. Facts route by weight; nothing important lives in only one head.": "agent 最大的残障:session 一结束,知识就没了。我的答案是分层——身份文件放\"法律\",常驻事实文件设 7 天准入测试,向量库(Mnemosyne,3,700+ 条)接长尾,Obsidian 做人工沉淀层。事实按权重路由;重要的东西绝不只活在一个脑袋里。", "Tokens aren't free": "token 不是免费的", "Every dev command an agent runs burns context. A filtering proxy (RTK) strips the noise before the model sees it — 75M+ tokens measured saved. Scheduled scripts that need no judgment run with no LLM at all. At home, a tiered router sends routine work to budget models and saves the heavyweight for deep reasoning. Same principle at every scale: pay for thinking, not for typing.": "agent 跑的每条 dev 命令都在烧上下文。一层过滤代理(RTK)在模型看到之前把噪音剥掉——实测省下 75M+ tokens。不需要判断的定时任务干脆不用 LLM 跑。在家里,分层路由把日常活派给便宜模型,重推理才请重型选手。同一个原则贯穿所有尺度:为思考付钱,不为打字付钱。", "Plausible is not correct": "像样 ≠ 正确", "Models produce answers that look right. That's why nothing merges without a human gate, every memory write shows a receipt, and the failure file above exists. Trust is a budget — spend it on verification, not on hope.": "模型产出的是\"看起来对\"的答案。所以任何东西不过人工闸门不许 merge,每次记忆写入都要出示收据,上面那份失败档案也因此存在。信任是预算——花在验证上,不要花在侥幸上。", "Good process doesn't repeat itself": "好流程不该重复自己", "Anything done twice becomes a versioned skill. Some we adopted from the community and adapted — credited, not claimed. Some we built from scratch: the delivery pipeline, the review roles, the repo router. The test is always the same: would a new teammate — human or agent — do this right on day one?": "做过两遍的事就该变成有版本的 skill。有些是从社区拿来再改造的——署名,不冒领;有些是从零自建的:交付管线、角色评审、repo 路由。检验标准永远是同一条:一个新同事——不管是人还是 agent——第一天照着做,能不能做对?", "The stack will change. The constraints won't.": "工具会换,约束不会。", "Build for the constraints.": "为约束而建。", "Henry Lee — Backend Team Lead": "Henry Lee — 后端 Team Lead", "Backend Team Lead": "后端 Team Lead", ".": "里长出来的。", "Hi — I'm Henry. I take backend platforms from a legacy monolith to contract-first gRPC microservices — the systems behind millions of daily transactions — and I lead the team that runs them.": "嗨,我是 Henry。我把后端平台从老单体带到契约先行的 gRPC 微服务——每天数百万笔交易背后的系统——并带着运营它的团队。", "7 years": "7 年", "Millions of transactions/day, audited": "每天数百万笔交易,全程审计", "every transaction, checked and logged": "每一笔交易,都检查并留痕", "50k → 400k+ users": "50k → 400k+ 用户", "users never noticed — which was the job": "用户毫无察觉——这正是目标", "Get in touch": "联系我", "See the work": "看作品", "featured work": "精选工作", "Featured": "精选", "Case 01": "案例 01", "The transaction backbone": "交易主干", "Every financial transaction on the platform passes through it — I took it from a legacy monolith to a contract-first service.": "平台上每一笔资金操作都从它经过——我把它从 legacy monolith 带到了 contract-first 服务。", "idempotent by construction": "幂等 by construction", "self-serve SDK": "自助 SDK", "Millions of transactions a day, and if it goes down the whole platform stops. I rebuilt it from a legacy monolith onto gRPC + durable workflows — idempotency by construction, so a retry can only return the record it already made — and made integration a self-serve SDK that cut new-type onboarding from 30–60 minutes to two.": "每天数百万笔交易,一旦它挂掉,整个平台停摆。我把它从 legacy monolith 重建到 gRPC + durable workflow——幂等 by construction,所以 retry 只可能拿回它已经创建的那条记录——并把接入做成一个自助 SDK,新类型上手从 30–60 分钟压到两分钟。", "Read the case study →": "读完整案例 →", "Case 02": "案例 02", "Scaling a platform, live": "平台扩容,线上完成", "50k → 400k+ users and still climbing — the job was making sure nobody noticed.": "50k → 400k+ 用户,仍在增长——我的工作是让所有人毫无察觉。", "measured before tuning": "先测量再调优", "replaced live": "线上替换", "every step revertible": "每一步都可 revert", "As the platform grew, ID generation, notification fan-out and blocking scans each hit the old architecture's limits — an outage stops every transaction. I measured where the time actually went, then replaced each mechanism in production: no downtime, users online, every step revertible.": "随着平台增长,ID 生成、通知 fan-out、阻塞式扫描接连撞上旧架构的上限——一次宕机就停掉所有交易。我先量清楚时间到底花在哪,再在生产上把每个机制逐个换掉:没有停机,用户全程在线,每一步都可 revert。", "Case 03": "案例 03", "Real-time support platform — from zero to clean handoff": "实时客服平台——从零到干净交接", "The first production service on a new stack — every pattern I set became the template others copied.": "新栈上的第一个生产服务——我立下的每个模式都成了别人照抄的模板。", "first on the new stack": "新栈第一个生产服务", "buy the base, build the moat": "买底座,自建 moat", "solo → team → clean handoff": "单人 → 团队 → 干净交接", "AI-assisted support with human takeover, built solo on a stack nobody had shipped to production yet. I bought the messaging base and self-built only the differentiators — routing, AI-to-human handoff, back-office — grew it to a two-person team, and handed it off clean. Being the pilot meant my patterns became the template every later service copied.": "带人工接管的 AI 客服,一个人在谁都没上过生产的技术栈上从零做起。我买下 messaging 底座,只自建差异化层——路由、AI 转人工的 handoff、后台——把团队扩到两人,再干净交接。作为 pilot,我的模式成了后续每个服务照抄的模板。", "More work": "更多工作", "Cross-stack mission pipeline — three languages, exactly-once →": "为跨栈发奖 pipeline 设计的 exactly-once 可靠性层 →", "Account-change ingestion — over ten million records a day, 10+ sources →": "亲手搭建平台量级最猛的数据路径——每天上千万条记录,10+ 来源 →", "Crypto payment rails — two years, three wallet protocols →": "加密货币支付通道——每一个交易边界上的 fintech 能力 →", "Reporting engine &amp; regulatory delivery →": "六年间平台的报表引擎,在 BI 团队出现之前 →", "All seven systems →": "全部七个系统 →", "Millions": "数百万", "transactions a day, audited": "每天审计的交易数", "daily users, from 50k (climbing)": "日活用户,从 50k 起(仍在涨)", "person team, two stacks": "人的团队,两代技术栈", "5 partner teams coordinated per project · 6 domains, two stacks · 80% coverage gate, enforced · weekly release train, full regression · 16 features shipped through my AI pipeline": "每个项目协调 5 个合作团队 · 6 个域,两代技术栈 · 80% 覆盖率门槛,强制执行 · 每周发版,全量回归 · 16 个功能经我的 AI pipeline 上线", "at altitude": "从高处看", "Systems,": "系统,", "Beyond any single feature — the decomposition, the platform, and the discipline to run it.": "超越任何单个功能——拆解、平台,以及运行它的纪律。", "Decomposed a legacy monolith into gRPC microservices.": "把老单体拆成 gRPC 微服务。", "Growth forced the rewrite — millions of transactions a day, ~1,000/s and still climbing past what the old architecture could hold. I led the migration of the platform's most critical flows onto a new NestJS/gRPC + Temporal stack: framework first, dead code retired on the way, the cutover carried by the SDK with endpoint-level fallback. Migration as modernization, with a rollback built into every step.": "是增长逼出来的重构——每天数百万笔交易、峰值 ~1,000/s 还在往上爬,老架构撑不住了。我带队把平台最关键的流程迁到新的 NestJS/gRPC + Temporal 栈:框架先行、迁移途中清理死码、切流由 SDK 承载并做 endpoint 级降级回退。迁移即现代化,每一步都内建回退。", "Built the contract-first platform the team ships on.": "搭起团队据以交付的契约先行平台。", "Proto-first by contract: one": "proto-first、契约先行:一份", "generates the gRPC types the SDK and every service share, so integration is one import with zero boilerplate. Adding a new request type went from a 30–60-minute, person-dependent process to a": "生成 SDK 与所有服务共享的 gRPC 类型,接入就是一个 import、零样板。新增一个请求类型,从要人翻代码、等 merge 的 30–60 分钟,变成", "two-minute self-serve": "两分钟自助", "form — pull request, publish, semantic versioning, changelog, notify. 100+ published versions; 200+ request types run through one base workflow. Developer enablement, not just a library.": "表单——pull request、发版、语义化版本、changelog、通知。100+ 已发布版本;200+ 请求类型跑在一个 base workflow 上。这是 developer enablement,不只是一个库。", "Ran it with production-grade observability.": "用生产级可观测性把它跑起来。", "What I watch every morning: queue backlog, workflow retries, database load, slow queries, CPU/memory spikes and leaks — on Grafana, with Aliyun SLS for log-based alerting and incident triage, OpenTelemetry traces and Prometheus metrics underneath. Graceful shutdown is a non-negotiable readiness gate — it came out of a real incident.": "我每天早上盯的:队列积压、workflow 重试、数据库负载、慢查询、CPU/内存尖峰与泄漏——都在 Grafana 上,配合阿里云 SLS 做基于日志的告警与线上排查,底层是 OpenTelemetry 链路和 Prometheus 指标。优雅停机是不可妥协的 readiness gate——它是从一次真实事故里长出来的规则。", "Index first, cache second": "先索引,后缓存", ": queries that timed out on a single day of data now scan a 30-day window.": ":当年查一天数据都超时的查询,如今随便查 30 天窗口。", "how i work": "我怎么工作", "How I": "我怎么", "Principles first, tasks second. The systems are half the job — the other half is building the people who build them.": "先讲原则,再谈任务。系统只是工作的一半——另一半是把做系统的人带出来。", "Price the risk before pricing the work.": "先给风险定价,再给工作量定价。", "The first question is never \"how long will it take\" — it's \"what breaks if this is wrong, and who feels it?\" Failure cost decides engineering rigor.": "第一个问题从来不是「要做多久」,而是「这东西错了会坏什么,谁会感觉到?」失败成本决定工程强度。", "Grow owners, not task-takers.": "培养 owner,不是接任务的人。", "Each engineer owns a domain end-to-end — requirements negotiation with business included.": "每个工程师端到端 own 一个域——连和业务谈需求都包括在内。", "Command the incident, then make it pay rent.": "先指挥事故,再让它交房租。", "Roll back first, diagnose second — then the incident pays: a playbook, a release rule, a report upward. Our risk-alerting pipeline was born from": "先 rollback,再排查——然后让事故交出回报:一份 playbook、一条发版规则、一份向上同步的报告。我们的风控告警 pipeline,就是从", "a single missed charge": "一次漏扣费", "Design for the next change, not this delivery.": "为下一次变更设计,而不是为这次交付。", "What business will tune later becomes configuration, not code — a feature request becomes an ops change, not a deploy.": "业务以后会想调的部分做成配置,而不是代码——一个新需求变成一次运维改动,而不是一次 deploy。", "Decompose by ownership, not by ticket.": "按 ownership 拆解,而不是按 ticket。", "Contracts split before anyone writes code — a cross-cutting feature once landed across five repositories in one day.": "写代码之前契约先拆好——一个横切五个仓库的功能,曾在一天内落地。", "Decide with evidence, commit with a rollback.": "用证据做决定,带着 rollback 去执行。", "Big choices get benchmarks and proofs of concept — one analytics-store evaluation ran 30 queries × 50 rounds across three engines before we committed.": "大的选型要 benchmark 和概念验证(POC)——一次分析型存储选型,三个引擎各跑 30 条查询 × 50 轮才拍板。", "Turn work into leverage.": "把工作变成杠杆。", "Anything done twice becomes a tool — integration SDKs, incident playbooks, an AI diagnosis bot the whole team runs.": "任何做过两次的事都要变成工具——集成 SDK、事故 playbook、全队都在用的 AI 诊断 bot。", "Calibrate the challenge.": "校准挑战的难度。", "Stretch without drowning — I watch where people stall and nudge; I don't grab the keyboard.": "要有拉伸,但不能淹死——我看他们卡在哪就点一下,不抢键盘。", "Pair temperaments, not just skills.": "搭配性格,不只搭配技能。", "A meticulous slow-mover next to a fast pusher who gets careless — tuned like any other system, re-tuned when they drift.": "一个细致但慢的人,配一个推得快但容易糙的人——像调任何系统一样调搭配,漂了就再调。", "Keep a floating seat.": "留一个机动位。", "One engineer goes wherever the pressure is — that seat is how I grew up, so I built it into the team on purpose.": "一个工程师,哪里压力大就去哪里——我自己就是在这个位置上长大的,所以特意把它做进了团队。", "Trade one deadline for the next ten.": "用一个 deadline 换后面十个。", "Build the base once and the next ten requests become configuration — a \"no\" always ships with its reason and its alternative.": "地基打一次,后面十个需求就都变成配置——每个「不」都带着理由和替代方案一起出口。", "about": "关于", "About": "关于", "me": "我", "Seven years ago I joined a high-traffic transaction platform as a full-stack dev. It grew — and went down a few times along the way. I was the firefighter, then the one hand-picked to pioneer a new stack, then the owner of the platform's most critical module — and now I lead the team that runs its core.": "七年前,我以全栈工程师的身份加入一个高并发交易平台。它一路在长——中间也挂过几次。我先是救火的人,后来被点名去开荒新技术栈,再后来接手平台最关键的模块——现在带着团队负责它的核心。", "I care about two things: systems that don't drop a transaction, and engineers who outgrow the tasks I give them.": "我在意两件事:系统不丢交易,工程师能长到超出我交给他们的任务。", "Now: raising a self-hosted Hermes agent (": "现在:在养一个 self-hosted 的 Hermes agent(", "it maintains this very site": "这个网站就是它在维护", "), going deeper on Rust and stream processing, and writing down what production taught me.": "),继续深入 Rust 和流处理,顺便把生产环境教我的东西写下来。", "experience": "经历", "A high-concurrency transaction platform, 2019 → present — engineer to Backend Team Lead.": "一个 高并发交易平台,2019 → 至今——从工程师到后端 Team Lead。", "Where this happened →": "这些都发生在哪 →", "core stack": "核心技术栈", "TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC · MongoDB · Redis · Temporal · Pulsar —": "TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC · MongoDB · Redis · Temporal · Pulsar ——", "full tiers →": "完整分层 →", "contact": "联系", "Get in": "联系", "touch": "我", "Alor Setar, Malaysia · UTC+8 · remote-ready": "马来西亚 亚罗士打 · UTC+8 · 可远程", "Personal Lab — Henry Lee": "个人实验室 — Henry Lee", "personal lab": "个人实验室", "Personal": "个人", "What I build when nobody's paying me to.": "没人付钱我也在做的东西。", "Hermes — a self-hosted agent": "Hermes——一个 self-hosted 的 agent", "Hermes Agent — Nous Research's open-source framework — running bare in WSL2 on my home server since May 2026, reachable through Telegram and WhatsApp gateways. Memory is layered: SOUL.md / MEMORY.md / USER.md carry identity and standing law (a fact must survive a 7-day admission test to get in), while Mnemosyne — vector memory on SQLite + embeddings — holds 3,700+ entries and counting for on-demand recall. 73 skills and 7 cron jobs do real work: a daily news brief, pre-market trading levels, a nightly memory digest, weekly memory consolidation, a monthly self-audit — and it built and maintains this very site. Same rule as at work: the agent does the miles, a human owns the gate.": "Hermes Agent——Nous Research 的开源框架——自 2026 年 5 月起裸装在我家用服务器的 WSL2 里,通过 Telegram 和 WhatsApp 网关随叫随到。记忆是分层的:SOUL.md / MEMORY.md / USER.md 承载身份和长期法条(一条事实要通过「7 天准入测试」才准进),Mnemosyne——建在 SQLite + embeddings 上的向量记忆——存着 3,700+ 条还在涨的条目,按需召回。73 个 skills 和 7 个 cron 任务干的是真活:每日新闻简报、开盘前交易点位、每晚记忆 digest、每周记忆整合、每月自查——这个网站也是它做的、它在维护。和公司里同一条规则:路让 agent 跑,门归人来把。", "73 skills": "73 个 skills", "3.7k+ memories": "3.7k+ 条记忆", "7 cron jobs": "7 个 cron 任务", "running since May 2026": "自 2026 年 5 月运行至今", "Mnemosyne memory": "Mnemosyne 记忆", "Scalp analyzer": "Scalp 分析器", "A live US-stock scalping analyzer in Python, run against a local Moomoo OpenD instance with yfinance as the fallback feed. It pulls 1m/5m/15m candles, computes EMA/MACD/RSI and session-anchored VWAP with pandas + ta, and checks seven classic setups — opening-range breakout, VWAP bounce, bull flag — with a confluence checklist and a 0–10 safety score that penalizes lunch chop and fading momentum. Wired up as a Claude Code skill, so \"check NVDA\" returns an entry/target/stop card. The pipeline is deliberately linear — feed → candles → checks → score → card — so when a reading looks wrong there is exactly one stage to inspect. Analysis only — every order is placed by hand.": "一个用 Python 写的美股 scalp 实时分析器,对着本地 Moomoo OpenD 实例跑,yfinance 做兜底数据源。它拉 1m/5m/15m K 线,用 pandas + ta 算 EMA/MACD/RSI 和以当日开盘锚定的 VWAP,检查七种经典形态——开盘区间突破、VWAP 反弹、bull flag——配一张 confluence 清单和一个 0–10 的安全分,午间震荡和动能衰减都会扣分。包装成了 Claude Code skill,一句「check NVDA」就返回一张 entry/target/stop 卡片。pipeline 刻意做成线性——feed → candles → checks → score → card——读数不对时,要查的环节只会有一个。只做分析——每一笔订单都是手动下的。", "yfinance fallback": "yfinance 兜底", "Stock sentry": "股票哨兵", "My biggest personal build: an AI trading assistant living in Telegram — python-telegram-bot at the front, the OpenAI API behind a multi-agent pipeline — analyzer, technical analyst, strategy generator, backtester, final decision — with Finnhub and yfinance for market data, a Streamlit backoffice, deployed on Zeabur. The agents run as a fixed chain — each one's output is the next one's input — so a verdict is traceable back through the backtest, strategy and analysis stages that produced it. Strategies live in a JSON skill library: the orchestrator matches them to market conditions, ranks them by tracked performance, and feeds trade outcomes back in. Every answer is forced into a tight format: verdict, entry, target, stop, one reason. About 8k lines of Python.": "我最大的个人项目:一个住在 Telegram 里的 AI 交易助手——前面是 python-telegram-bot,后面是 OpenAI API 驱动的多 agent pipeline——分析器、技术分析、策略生成、回测、最终决策——行情数据来自 Finnhub 和 yfinance,配一个 Streamlit 后台,部署在 Zeabur 上。agent 按固定链条跑——上一个的输出就是下一个的输入——所以每个结论都能沿着产生它的回测、策略、分析各阶段追回去。策略放在一个 JSON skill 库里:orchestrator 按市场状态匹配策略,按跟踪到的表现排序,再把交易结果喂回去。每个回答都被强制成紧凑格式:结论、entry、target、stop、一条理由。约 8k 行 Python。", "AI home server": "AI 家用服务器", "No longer a blueprint — a Minisforum UM890 Pro (Ryzen 9 8945HS, 32GB) now runs 24/7 in my living room: Windows 11 with WSL2 Ubuntu, Hermes installed bare-metal inside, plus a FastAPI trading server and a static daily-news page. Access is Tailscale-only — zero open ports, with a Windows portproxy bridging into WSL. The honest lesson: local models were the plan, and they lost — Ollama running Qwen 2.5 7B and Llama 3.1 8B couldn't keep up with multi-round tool calling on CPU-only inference, so a tiered router now sends routine work to budget cloud models and reserves a heavyweight for deep reasoning. The security model survived contact intact: sandboxed agent, outbound allowlist, low-privilege accounts per service, and a green/yellow/red delegation table — banking credentials stay red, forever.": "已经不是蓝图了——一台 Minisforum UM890 Pro(Ryzen 9 8945HS,32GB)现在 24/7 跑在我的客厅里:Windows 11 加 WSL2 Ubuntu,Hermes 裸装在里面,外加一个 FastAPI 交易服务和一个静态每日新闻页。访问只走 Tailscale——零开放端口,由 Windows portproxy 桥进 WSL。诚实的教训:本地模型本来是计划,但它们输了——Ollama 跑 Qwen 2.5 7B 和 Llama 3.1 8B,纯 CPU 推理跟不上多轮 tool calling,所以现在由一个分层 router 把日常工作发给便宜的云端模型,把重型模型留给深度推理。安全模型倒是完好地经受住了现实:沙箱里的 agent、出站白名单、每个服务一个低权限账号,以及一张绿/黄/红委派表——银行凭证永远是红,永远。", "Tailscale-only": "仅 Tailscale 可达", "Ollama → tiered cloud": "Ollama → 分层云端", "24/7 since May 2026": "24/7,自 2026 年 5 月", "Personal financial planning system": "个人财务规划系统", "A bilingual (EN / 中文) financial-planning app I built this year to run my own numbers: long-term financial projections at three lifestyle levels, mortgage-acceleration math, portfolio allocation with ten-year projections, and a cash &amp; position tracker. Everything persists in localStorage with JSON export — no accounts, no server. Vanilla JavaScript, no framework — a tool for one user should stay simple enough to maintain in one evening.": "一个我今年做来算自己那本账的双语(EN / 中文)财务规划应用:三个生活档位的长期财务推演、提前还房贷的数学、带十年推演的资产配置,外加一个现金与持仓追踪器。所有数据都存在 localStorage,支持 JSON 导出——没有账号,没有服务器。Vanilla JavaScript,不用框架——给一个用户用的工具,就该简单到一个晚上能维护完。", "View on GitHub ↗": "在 GitHub 查看 ↗", "Workflow backbone — Henry Lee": "Workflow 主干 — Henry Lee", "case 01 / 07": "案例 01 / 07", "The transaction backbone — from a legacy monolith to a contract-first service": "交易主干——从 legacy monolith 到 contract-first 服务", "Every financial transaction on the platform passes through it — millions a day, and it can never process one twice.": "平台上每一笔资金操作都从它经过——每天数百万笔,而它永远不能把同一笔处理两次。", "millions of transactions/day": "每天数百万笔交易", "2-min self-serve SDK": "2 分钟自助 SDK", "200+ types · one base workflow": "200+ 种类型 · 一条 base workflow", "Situation": "背景", "Every financial transaction on the platform — withdrawal, top-up, loyalty reward, configuration change — must pass one audited create → review → approve → execute lifecycle. The legacy implementation was tightly coupled inside a monolith; every consumer re-implemented its own wiring.": "平台上每一笔金融交易——提现、充值、奖励、配置变更——都必须走同一条带审计的 create → review → approve → execute 生命周期。旧实现和单体紧紧耦在一起,每个接入方都要自己重新实现一遍接线。", "Constraint": "约束", "This is the platform's single point of trust: production pushes millions of transactions a day through it — into the tens of millions at peak — and a duplicate execution means a transaction is processed twice.": "这是整个平台唯一的信任锚点:生产环境每天有 数百万笔交易从这里过,一次重复执行,就意味着一笔交易被处理了两次。", "Approach": "做法", "Rebuilt it as a gRPC microservice orchestrated by Temporal: one generic durable workflow runs every request type, with business extension points as child-workflow slots. Idempotency is structural — the workflow ID doubles as the creation key, so a retried step returns the existing record instead of creating twice. Integration became a published SDK: any service registers an executor with one import; adding a new request type is a self-service CI form, not a queue on my desk. 100+ SDK releases with disciplined semantic versioning.": "把它重建成由 Temporal 编排的 gRPC 微服务:一条通用的持久化 workflow 跑所有请求类型,业务扩展点做成 child-workflow 插槽。幂等是结构性的——workflow ID 兼任创建 key,所以被 retry 的步骤只会拿回已存在的记录,而不是创建第二条。接入变成对外发布的 SDK:任何服务一个 import 就能注册 executor;新增一种请求类型是一张自助 CI 表单,而不是排在我桌上的队。100+ 次 SDK 发布,严格遵循语义化版本。", "Outcome": "结果", "Millions of transactions a day in production. Duplicate execution is prevented by construction rather than caught after the fact. New-type integration went from a 30-to-60-minute, person-dependent process to two-minute self-service.": "生产环境每天数百万笔交易。重复执行由构造防住,而不是事后去抓。新类型接入从一个 30–60 分钟、依赖特定人的流程,变成了两分钟自助。", "audited lifecycle — every transaction": "audited lifecycle — every transaction", "War stories": "实战故事", "The redemption that didn't charge": "没扣费的那次兑换", "Customer support found it before any dashboard did: a reward-redemption flow was handing out value without deducting the balance. A pre-charge step in the workflow was being skipped — silently.": "最先发现的是客服,不是任何一块 dashboard:一条奖励兑换流程在发放价值,却没有扣减余额。workflow 里的预扣费步骤被跳过了——而且是静默跳过。", "Rollback first, debug second. The trail led to a shared contract file that had quietly fallen behind on one branch; a routine package upgrade activated the stale copy. Tests never caught it, because the change came from a different kind of project — the classic blind spot where two individually safe changes combine into one unsafe system.": "先 rollback,再排查。线索指向一份共享的契约文件:它在某个分支上悄悄落后了,一次例行的包升级激活了这份过期副本。测试从没抓到它,因为改动来自另一类项目——两个各自安全的变更,组合成一个不安全的系统,是最经典的盲区。", "The fixes were systemic, not local: the workflow fails loudly if the pre-charge step doesn't run; every release regression-tests every transaction path, no exceptions; and the incident report went up and out — the whole team knows this failure shape now.": "修复是系统性的,不是局部的:预扣费步骤没跑,workflow 就大声失败;每次发版都对每一条涉及交易的路径做回归测试,没有例外;事故报告向上、向外同步——全队现在都认识这种失败形态。", "One more thing grew out of it: the first version of our risk-alerting pipeline — every redemption event published onto the event bus, alerting the risk team in chat. Detection first, automation later. Incidents are cheapest when they compile into systems.": "还有一样东西从这次事故里长了出来:我们风控告警 pipeline 的第一版——每个兑换事件都发布到事件总线上,在聊天里告警风控团队。先做检测,自动化后置。事故最便宜的归宿,是把它编译进系统。", "The signal that arrived too early": "来得太早的 signal", "Our workflows accept human decisions and third-party confirmations as signals — and one day a callback landed before our own state had finished persisting. The workflow received a signal for a record that, from its point of view, didn't exist yet; worse, on replay the interleaving wasn't deterministic. The fix was structural: signals are buffered until the state they refer to has landed, and every behavioural change to the workflow code ships behind a versioned patch marker — so workflows already running mid-history replay the exact logic they started with, while new ones take the new path. In durable workflows, a code deploy is an event your running history has to survive.": "我们的 workflow 把人工决策和第三方确认都当作 signal 接收——有一天,一个回调在我们自己的状态还没持久化完成之前就到了。workflow 收到了一个 signal,而它指向的记录在 workflow 看来还不存在;更糟的是,replay 时这个交错顺序并不确定。修复是结构性的:signal 会被缓冲,直到它指向的状态落地为止;并且 workflow 代码的每一次行为变更都带着版本化的 patch 标记上线——历史跑到一半的 workflow 会 replay 它们启动时的那套逻辑,新的才走新路径。在持久化 workflow 里,一次代码 deploy,就是你正在运行的历史必须活过去的一个事件。", "The retry that had to return the same record": "必须拿回同一条记录的 retry", "The engine retries failed steps — that's the point of it. But on a transaction path, a retried create is a potential duplicate record, and a duplicate record is a transaction processed twice. So creation isn't guarded by a check bolted on afterwards; it's guarded by construction: the workflow ID doubles as the record's creation key, and every create looks up before it writes — a retry finds the record its first attempt made and returns it. Updates carry status guards, and illegal state transitions throw instead of writing. When the failure mode is financial, idempotency can't be a best effort; it has to be impossible to get wrong.": "引擎会 retry 失败的步骤——这本来就是它存在的意义。但在资金路径上,一次被 retry 的 create 就是一条潜在的重复记录,而一条重复记录就是一笔交易被处理了两次。所以创建不是靠事后补一个检查来守护,而是由构造守护:workflow ID 兼任记录的创建 key,每次 create 都先查再写——retry 找到第一次尝试创建的那条记录,把它返回。更新带状态守卫,非法的状态迁移直接抛错而不是写入。当失败模式涉及资金时,幂等不能是尽力而为;它必须是不可能做错。", "Four environments, one engine": "四个环境,一个引擎", "Several environments shared one workflow-engine cluster, and workers began stealing each other's tasks — a developer's local worker could quietly pick up and fail a task that belonged to a shared test lane. The fix was a naming discipline, not more hardware: task-queue names resolve per environment — production gets a fixed name, local runs are suffixed with the developer's identity, test lanes with the environment. Boring, but it ended a whole class of \"works on my machine, breaks your test run\" ghosts. Shared infrastructure needs namespacing before it needs capacity.": "几个环境共用一个 workflow 引擎集群,worker 开始互相偷任务——一个开发者本地的 worker 可能悄悄捡走并搞挂一条属于共享测试通道的任务。修复靠的是命名纪律,不是更多硬件:task-queue 名称按环境解析——生产用固定名,本地运行带上开发者身份后缀,测试通道带环境后缀。很无聊,但它终结了一整类「我机器上是好的,你的测试却挂了」的幽灵问题。共享基础设施先需要 namespacing,然后才需要容量。", "← All work": "← 全部工作", "Next: Scaling 50k → 400k+ users →": "下一篇:平台扩容 50k → 400k+ 用户 →", "Crypto payment rails — Henry Lee": "加密货币支付通道 — Henry Lee", "case 06 / 07": "案例 06 / 07", "Building the platform's crypto payment rails — a fintech capability at every transaction boundary": "搭建平台的加密货币支付通道——每一个交易边界上的 fintech 能力", "A two-year epic threading fiat↔stablecoin conversion through every transaction boundary on the platform — where a precision slip is a real financial loss.": "一个两年期的 epic,把法币↔stablecoin 的转换织进平台每一个资金边界——在那里,一次精度失误就是一笔真实的资金损失。", "2-engineer pair, 2 years": "2 人搭档,2 年", "exact-decimal balances": "精确小数的余额", "The platform needed cryptocurrency deposits and withdrawals alongside fiat — conversion at every transaction boundary, on a platform where some third-party providers couldn't hold crypto at all.": "平台需要在法币之外支持加密货币的充值与提现——每一处交易边界都要做转换,而且有些第三方 provider 根本持有不了加密货币。", "I drove the payments side for two years as half of a two-engineer pair (alongside the team's assistant lead): wallet protocol integrations (OMNI, ERC-20, TRC-20), stablecoin deposits and withdrawals, and fiat↔stablecoin conversion threaded through every transaction boundary. Provider heterogeneity was the judgment call — some providers couldn't hold the stablecoin at all, so I absorbed the difference in one cross-cutting compatibility layer rather than leaking it into every call site — with exact-decimal handling at the wallet edges, where a rounding error becomes a real discrepancy.": "支付这条线我推了两年,和团队的副手搭档、两个工程师负责:钱包协议集成(OMNI、ERC-20、TRC-20)、stablecoin 的充值与提现,以及织进每一个交易边界的法币↔stablecoin 转换。provider 的异构是这里的判断点——有些 provider 根本持有不了 stablecoin,所以我把差异吸收进一个横切的兼容层,而不是让它泄漏到每一个调用点——钱包边缘全部用精确小数处理,因为在那里,一个舍入误差就是一笔真实的账目差异。", "Crypto rails went live across every payment flow; later currencies reused the same config-driven paths instead of re-opening them.": "加密货币通道在每一条支付流上都上线了;后来新增的币种直接复用同一套配置驱动的路径,而不用再把它们重新打开。", "← Previous: Transaction-record ingestion": "← 上一篇:交易记录接入", "All work": "全部工作", "Next: Reporting engine &amp; regulatory delivery →": "下一篇:报表引擎与监管报送 →", "Transaction-record ingestion — Henry Lee": "交易记录接入 — Henry Lee", "case 05 / 07": "案例 05 / 07", "Hand-building the platform's highest-volume data path — over ten million records a day": "亲手搭建平台量级最猛的数据路径——每天上千万条记录", "Every balance change a user sees, pulled from 10+ heterogeneous systems most of which my team didn't own — aligned record by record, always adding up.": "用户看到的每一次余额变动,拉自 10+ 个异构系统、其中大多数还不归我团队所有——逐条对齐,永远对得上账。", "over ten million records/day": "每天上千万条记录", "10+ heterogeneous sources": "10+ 个异构来源", "cross-team alignment": "跨团队对齐", "hot / cold split": "冷热拆分", "The platform's most demanding data path — a superset of the transaction backbone. Every balance change a user sees must be complete, ordered, and fast to query, but records originate from 10+ heterogeneous sources that disagree on shape, timing, and delivery guarantees: millions/day through the audited workflow path, the rest streaming straight from providers and internal systems most of which my team didn't own.": "平台上要求最苛刻的数据路径——是交易主干的超集。用户看到的每一次余额变动都必须完整、有序、查得快,但记录来自 10+ 个异构来源,它们在形状、时序和投递保证上各说各话:每天数百万笔走带审计的 workflow 路径,其余的直接从 provider 和内部系统流进来,而这些系统大多不归我团队所有。", "Hand-built the ingestion pipeline — composing a stream processor with a durable-workflow engine — and chose an analytics-oriented store deliberately, so long-window analytics volume wouldn't contend with production reads and writes for resources: hot recent history on the operational store with covering indexes; long-window analytics offloaded to a columnar layer fed by the pipeline; source-specific shapes normalized at the boundary, with per-source caching and channel-aware routing. The hard part was cross-team alignment, not code: I scanned every transaction path across two generations of the system, drove the direction for the owning teams, and reconciled historical mismatches record by record where amounts didn't line up — and shipped it while learning the real-time analytics database and stream stack on the fly, in two weeks.": "亲手搭建这条接入 pipeline——把一个 stream processor 和一个 durable-workflow 引擎组合起来——并刻意选了一个偏分析的存储,让长窗口分析量不与生产读写抢资源:热的近期历史放在业务库上,配 covering index;长窗口分析卸到由 pipeline 喂数的列式存储层;来源特有的形状在边界归一化,配上按来源的缓存和感知渠道的路由。真正难的是跨团队对齐,而不是写代码:我扫遍了新旧两代系统里的每一条资金路径,给各个 owner 团队指方向,在额度对不上的地方逐条补齐历史差异——而且是一边现学实时分析数据库和流处理栈、一边在两周内交付的。", "Over ten million records a day (climbing) ingested and queryable; recent-history reads stay fast while analytical queries stopped competing with production traffic.": "每天上千万条记录(仍在增长)接入并可查询;近期历史的读取保持快速,分析查询不再和生产流量抢资源。", "Most of the work was comparing numbers": "大部分工作,是在对数字", "Nobody tells you this about building an ingestion pipeline: the code is the quick part. For a long stretch of development, one record subtype ran as a permanent probe — continuously reconciled against its sources while everything else was still moving.": "做接入 pipeline,没人告诉你的一件事是:写代码是快的那部分。开发过程中有很长一段时间,一种记录子类型作为常驻探针在跑——在其他一切还在动的时候,持续和它的来源对账。", "Then the cross-checks widened: daily totals per record type compared against the analytics team's independent numbers, and per-user daily histories diffed record by record. When a figure disagreed, that was the day's work — trace which source dropped, duplicated or reshaped it, fix the boundary, backfill, compare again.": "然后交叉核对越铺越宽:每种记录类型的每日总数,对上分析团队独立算出的数字;每个用户的每日历史,逐条 diff。哪个数字对不上,那就是当天的活——追出是哪个来源丢了、重复了还是改了形状,修好边界,backfill,再对一遍。", "It's manual, it's unglamorous, and it's the only reason the number on a user's screen can be trusted. Correctness isn't a property you declare; it's one you keep re-earning.": "这活儿手工、不体面,但用户屏幕上那个数字之所以可信,靠的就是它。正确性不是一个宣布了就成立的属性,而是要不断重新挣来的。", "← Previous: Cross-stack mission pipeline": "← 上一篇:跨栈任务 pipeline", "Next: Crypto payment rails →": "下一篇:加密货币支付通道 →", "Cross-stack mission pipeline — Henry Lee": "跨栈任务 pipeline — Henry Lee", "case 04 / 07": "案例 04 / 07", "The exactly-once reliability layer for a cross-stack rewards pipeline": "为跨栈发奖 pipeline 设计的 exactly-once 可靠性层", "Four services, three languages, a reward path where a double-pay is real loss — I designed the layer that makes payout happen exactly once, with zero changes to the legacy system.": "4 个服务、3 种语言、一条重复发放就是真实损失的发奖路径——我设计了让发放恰好一次的那层,旧系统 0 改动。", "4 services · 3 languages": "4 个服务 · 3 种语言", "exactly-once, layered": "exactly-once,分层实现", "0 legacy changes": "旧系统 0 改动", "pre-prod verified": "pre-prod 验证", "Marketing wanted automatic, time-boxed missions for users close to their next loyalty tier: detect them in real time, run a 7-day window, grant the upgrade instantly on success.": "市场团队想给接近下一个忠诚度等级的用户做自动的、限时的任务:实时发现他们,跑一个 7 天窗口,达成后即时发放升级。", "The reward path is financially sensitive: a duplicate grant is a real loss, and events arrive at least-once from both the stream and the workflow engine — two independent sources of duplicates.": "发奖路径涉及资金:重复发放就是真实损失,而事件从流和 workflow 引擎两边都是 at-least-once 到达——两个互相独立的重复来源。", "Built the chain end-to-end across four services in three languages — the boundaries followed the platform's existing seams (the streaming platform, the workflow engine, the reward facade), composing proven engines instead of building new ones: a Java/Flink job filters the event stream and computes entry-anchored goals from a lookup table; a Rust + Temporal engine runs one durable workflow per user; a NestJS facade grants through the existing upgrade path — zero changes to legacy systems. Exactly-once is layered: an atomic claims ledger (one chance per user, tier, month) gates enrollment, and a human-readable idempotency key (`mission:user:tier:month`) gates the grant — debuggable at a glance in production. Thresholds live in exactly one place — producers broadcast unconditionally, so two repositories can never disagree about the same number.": "端到端把这条链做穿四个服务、三种语言——边界沿着平台现有的缝走(流处理平台、workflow 引擎、发奖 facade),组合已被验证的引擎,而不是造新的:一个 Java/Flink 作业过滤事件流,按查表计算以进入时刻为锚点的目标;一个 Rust + Temporal 引擎给每个用户跑一条持久 workflow;一个 NestJS facade 走现有升级路径发放——旧系统 0 改动。exactly-once 分层实现:一张原子的 claims 台账(每个用户、等级、月份只有一次机会)把住报名,一个人类可读的幂等 key(`mission:user:tier:month`)把住发放——生产上一眼就能排查。阈值只存在一个地方——生产者无条件广播,两个仓库永远不可能对同一个数字有分歧。", "Verified end-to-end against real production-like traffic in the pre-production lane — honest scope: it runs in pre-production (QAT), not production — with funnel metrics at every stage and a dry-run-by-default rollout I put through an outside red-team before calling it safe. The service decomposition wasn't mine to claim; my design was the reliability layer on top — exactly-once by an owned ledger and key. That layer, plus detect / orchestrate / grant with single-owner config, is the template for the next mission types.": "在 pre-production 通道里对着接近生产的真实流量做了端到端验证——范围诚实:它跑在预发布环境(QAT),不是生产——每一级都有漏斗指标,上线打法是 dry-run 默认开,我还请了外部 red-team 过一遍才说它安全。服务的切分不是我可以邀功的;我设计的是上面那层可靠性——靠自己 own 的台账和 key 做到 exactly-once。这一层,加上发现 / 编排 / 发放、配置单一 owner,成了下一批任务类型的模板。", "← Previous: Real-time support platform": "← 上一篇:实时客服平台", "Next: Transaction-record ingestion →": "下一篇:交易记录接入 →", "Reporting engine &amp; regulatory delivery — Henry Lee": "报表引擎与监管报送 — Henry Lee", "case 07 / 07": "案例 07 / 07", "The platform's reporting engine for six years — before there was a business-intelligence (BI) team": "六年间平台的报表引擎——在 BI 团队出现之前", "Multi-view analytics over million-row, long-window queries on the primary database — 140+ reporting changes, plus regulatory filings on time at millions of rows.": "在主库上跑百万行、长窗口查询的多视角分析——140+ 次报表变更,外加百万行级监管报送按时交付。", "millions of rows/day": "每天数百万行", "hard deadlines, met": "硬性期限,从未误期", "140+ reporting changes": "140+ 次报表变更", "Before a BI team existed, operations, partners, and management all needed data — and later, a regulator needed daily filings in exact formats: millions of rows per day, hard deadline, aggregated over long windows on the production database.": "在 BI 团队存在之前,运营、合作方、管理层都需要数据——后来监管方又要求按精确格式做每日报送:每天数百万行,期限是硬性的,还要在生产数据库上跑长时间窗口的 aggregation。", "Design": "设计", "Reporting numbers feed commercial reconciliation, so I optimized for both speed and correctness rather than trading one for the other — a precompute + recompute dual track: read from precomputed daily summaries for latency, keep a recompute window open so late corrections still land. An independent settlement process streams per-user transaction flows to workers in batches, landing those daily summaries; ad-hoc queries run tuned aggregation pipelines; the scheduler was rewritten for reliable 2-day recompute windows. For regulatory delivery, built the filing pipeline: million-row-per-file slicing, append-based FTP upload, stream batches tuned until multi-million-row days fit the window.": "报表数字要喂给商务对账,所以我 optimize for 又快又对、而不是二选一——预计算 + 重算的双轨:读取走预计算的每日汇总保延迟,同时留一个重算窗口,让事后的迟到修正也能落进去。一个独立的结算进程把每个用户的交易流按 batch 推给 worker,落成那些每日汇总;临时查询走调优过的 aggregation pipeline;调度器被重写以保证 2 天重算窗口的可靠性。监管报送这边,搭了整条报送 pipeline:按每文件一百万行切片,FTP 上传走 append 方式,stream batch 一路调到几百万行的日子也能塞进窗口。", "The platform had a working BI function before it had a BI team — the formal team later built on these foundations. Regulatory filings shipped on schedule at million-row scale; 140+ reporting changes over six years.": "平台在拥有 BI 团队之前,就先有了一个能用的 BI 职能——后来正式的团队就是在这套地基上继续建的。监管报送在百万行的规模上按时交付;六年里 140+ 次报表变更。", "← Previous: Crypto payment rails": "← 上一篇:加密货币支付通道", "Scaling 50k → 400k+ users — Henry Lee": "平台扩容:50k → 400k+ 用户 — Henry Lee", "case 02 / 07": "案例 02 / 07", "Keeping a high-concurrency transaction platform standing 50k → 400k+ users": "让一个 高并发交易平台在 50k → 400k+ 用户中屹立不倒", "I drove the re-architectures that kept the platform up as daily users climbed to 400k+ — replacing the ceilings one live single-point at a time.": "我主导了那些 re-architecture,在 日活爬到 400k+ 的过程中撑住平台——一次换掉一个线上单点。", "50k → 400k+, live": "50k → 400k+,线上完成", "collision-proof cutover": "cutover 偏移 +10 亿", "sub-second pushes": "亚秒级推送", "1 day → 30-day queries": "查询窗口 1 天 → 30 天", "Over four years the member management platform grew from 50k to 400k+, and growth kept finding the limits of the old mechanisms — a counter document in the database serialized every ID; notification fan-out stalled under load. More than once, the failure happened in production first.": "四年里平台从 50k 涨到 400k+,增长不断把旧机制的极限找出来——数据库里的一份 counter 文档把所有 ID 生成串行化;通知 fan-out 在高负载下卡死。不止一次,故障是先在生产上发生的。", "No rewrite budget, no downtime allowance — every fix had to land inside a weekly release train, live, with users on.": "没有重写的预算,也没有停机的余地——每个修复都必须塞进每周发版的节奏里,在线上落地,用户还在线。", "Every target was a live global single-point, so I optimized for reversibility over speed — small, individually revertible PRs shipped in series rather than one big-bang cutover. I championed bringing a distributed cache into the platform, then root-caused each bottleneck to its mechanism and replaced the mechanism, not the symptom: ID generation moved from a database counter to atomic Redis INCR — cut over with a +1-billion offset so old and new ranges could never collide; notification fan-out moved to Redis pub/sub (shipped, reverted on a production surprise, re-landed hardened); blocking full-set scans replaced with cursor-based SSCAN; a leaking in-memory config cache rebuilt with a 15-minute refresh cycle.": "每个改造对象都是线上全局单点,所以我 optimize for reversibility over speed——小而各自可 revert 的 PR 连发成序,而不是一次性 big-bang cutover。我提案把 distributed cache 推进平台,然后把每个瓶颈都追到它的机制层面,换掉机制、而不是治症状:ID 生成从数据库 counter 换成原子的 Redis INCR——cutover 带 +10 亿的偏移,新旧区间永远不可能相撞;通知 fan-out 迁到 Redis pub/sub(上线过,因生产意外 revert 过,加固后重新落地);阻塞式的全量扫描换成基于 cursor 的 SSCAN;一个泄漏的内存配置缓存重建成 15 分钟刷新一轮。", "The platform sustains 400k+ daily active users without the old failure modes. The patterns introduced (cache-aside, atomic counters, pub/sub fan-out) became house standards for modules built after.": "平台稳定支撑 400k+ 日活,旧的失败模式不再出现。这次引入的模式(cache-aside、原子计数、pub/sub fan-out)成了之后新模块的团队标准。", "The tuning months": "调优的那几个月", "Before this platform earned its Redis layer, it had to earn its database. The reporting layer predated any business-intelligence team — and one stretch of growth broke it visibly: operational reports stopped coming back at all, and on the busiest collection a query couldn't return even a single day's records without timing out.": "这个平台在配得上它的 Redis 层之前,得先配得上它的数据库。报表层比任何 BI 团队都出现得早——有一段增长期把它明晃晃地压垮了:运营报表干脆不再返回,最忙的那个 collection 上,一条查询连一天的记录都取不回来就超时。", "The months that followed were unglamorous: reading the slow-query log like a newspaper, matching covering indexes to the query shapes people actually ran (and deleting the indexes nobody did — on write-heavy collections an unused index is pure tax), rebuilding aggregation pipelines stage by stage, and moving text search off regex scans onto a proper search index.": "之后的几个月毫无光环:像读报纸一样读 slow-query 日志,给大家真正在跑的查询形状配上 covering index(再删掉没人用的索引——在写多的 collection 上,一个没用的索引就是纯税),把 aggregation pipeline 一段一段重建,把文本搜索从 regex 扫描搬到真正的搜索索引上。", "Thirty-day report windows came back comfortably on collections where one day used to time out. That work never made a release announcement — but every feature shipped since stands on it.": "30 天窗口的报表,在那些曾经连 1 天都超时的 collection 上轻松跑回来了。这些工作从没上过发版公告——但之后上线的每个功能都踩在它上面。", "Measure first, then argue": "先测量,再争论", "Push notifications were arriving late, and the room's instinct was to tune the WebSocket layer — it was the visible component. Before touching anything I measured where the time actually went, and the cost wasn't in the sockets at all: it was the fan-out loop behind them, delivering to every connection from one place. We moved fan-out to pub/sub so each instance delivers to its own connections, and pushes went sub-second. The loudest component is rarely the bottleneck; the profile decides, not the intuition.": "推送通知到得晚,屋里的直觉是去调 WebSocket 层——它是看得见的那个组件。动手之前我先量了时间到底花在哪,结果成本根本不在 socket 上:是它背后的 fan-out 循环,从一个地方向每条连接投递。我们把 fan-out 迁到 pub/sub,让每个实例投递自己的连接,推送就进了亚秒级。最吵的组件很少是瓶颈;profile 说了算,直觉不算。", "The revert that came back stronger": "回来更强的那次 revert", "The fan-out migration shipped — and production surprised us, so we reverted. The second landing looked different: instead of one big change, a series of small, individually revertible steps, each one hardened by what the first attempt had taught us. Nothing about the design was wrong; the delivery was. On a live transaction platform the unit of change has to equal the unit of rollback — that rule came out of this war and never left.": "fan-out 迁移上线了——生产给了我们一个意外,于是 revert。第二次落地长得完全不同:不再是一个大改动,而是一串小的、各自可 revert 的步骤,每一步都被第一次尝试教到的东西加固过。设计没有错;错的是交付方式。在一个跑着真实交易的线上平台,变更的单位必须等于 rollback 的单位——这条规则从这场仗里来,之后再没离开过。", "A billion-ID head start": "领先 10 亿个 ID 的起跑线", "ID generation had to move from a database counter to atomic increments in Redis — with users online and no maintenance window. Instead of choreographing a precise cutover between two live generators, we made collision impossible: the new range started one billion above the old counter, so both could run at once and never meet. Rollback was equally boring — point back at the old counter. When transactions are on the line, the clever solution is the one with nothing left to go wrong.": "ID 生成必须从数据库 counter 迁到 Redis 的原子自增——用户在线,没有维护窗口。与其在两个活着的生成器之间编排一次精准的 cutover,我们直接让碰撞不可能发生:新区间从旧 counter 之上 10 亿的位置起步,两边可以同时跑,永远碰不上。rollback 同样无聊——指回旧 counter 就行。当交易在盯着的时候,聪明的方案,是那个没有任何东西可以再出错的方案。", "← Previous: Workflow backbone": "← 上一篇:Workflow 主干", "Next: Real-time support platform →": "下一篇:实时客服平台 →", "Real-time support platform — Henry Lee": "实时客服平台 — Henry Lee", "case 03 / 07": "案例 03 / 07", "The first production service on a brand-new stack — from zero to clean handoff": "新栈上的第一个生产服务——从零到干净交接", "The pilot the whole stack migration was judged on — I built it solo, and every pattern I set became the template later services copied.": "整个技术栈迁移就看这个 pilot——我一个人从零建,我立下的每个模式都成了后续服务照抄的模板。", "became the template others copied": "成了别人照抄的模板", "The company needed AI-assisted customer conversations with human takeover — and had just decided on a new microservices stack no one had shipped to production yet. I was handed both problems at once.": "公司需要带人工接管的 AI 客服对话——而且刚刚敲定了一套谁都没上过生产的新微服务技术栈。两个问题一起塞给了我。", "Solo start; NestJS, gRPC, Temporal, Pulsar and an off-the-shelf messaging backbone — all new to me at once; the outcome would decide whether the company's migration was viable.": "单人起步;NestJS、gRPC、Temporal、Pulsar、一套现成的 messaging backbone——对我来说全是同时上手的新东西;做出来的结果,直接决定公司的迁移方案是否可行。", "Self-hosted an off-the-shelf messaging backbone as the message transport (the framework was the CTO's call; the data model and flows were mine), then built only the differentiators it doesn't have: an agent-routing queue encoding status > load > wait-time into a single Redis sorted-set score — banded so status always outranks load, and load outranks waiting time; assignment just reads the head of the queue; a mini back-office management system so agents see a member's account records, top-up / withdrawal history and permissions in one screen instead of switching systems; AI answers first — designed to absorb the repetitive ~70% of inquiries — with a 10-second race guard that hands the chat to a human whenever the model stalls or errors. Concurrency was the war — the score race and the duplicate-invite storm both have their own war stories below.": "Self-hosted 一套现成的 messaging backbone 做消息传输层(选这套框架是 CTO 的决定;数据模型和流程是我的),然后只自建有业务壁垒的差异化层:一个客服路由队列,把状态 &gt; 负载 &gt; 等待时长编码进一个 Redis sorted-set 分数——分数分段,状态永远压过负载,负载永远压过等待时长;派单只需要读队头;一个迷你后台,让客服在一个屏幕里看到用户的记录、历史和权限,不用来回切系统;AI 先答——设计目标就是消化掉重复性的 ~70% 咨询——配一个 10 秒的竞速保护,模型一卡壳或报错就把会话交给人。并发是这场仗的主战场:我把分数上的 read-modify-write 竞态重建成原子自增——生产又暴露出 Redis cluster 不吃 MULTI,当天就降级成纯原子操作——再用 per-room 锁挡住重复邀请客服的问题。", "First production service on the new stack — the pattern reference (config via Vault, contract-first gRPC, structured logging, graceful shutdown) that later services copied. Grew the team to two, handed the service to a maintenance team, later to the AI team. It now runs as a standalone multi-channel middleware.": "新技术栈上的第一个生产服务——后来的服务都在抄它的模式(Vault 管配置、契约先行的 gRPC、结构化日志、graceful shutdown)。团队扩到两人,服务先交给维护团队,后来交给 AI 团队。它现在作为一个独立的多渠道中间件在跑。", "The day the cluster said no": "集群说「不」的那天", "Queue positions lived as scores, and the original update was read-modify-write: read the score, compute in memory, write it back. Under concurrency two updates interleaved and one silently overwrote the other. I rebuilt the updates as atomic increments wrapped in a transaction — and then production revealed our Redis cluster wouldn't accept the transaction at all. Because the score design was banded — status, load and waiting time each own their own order of magnitude — every state change was already expressible as a single atomic increment, so we degraded to pure atomic ops the same day. A fix isn't done until it survives the real topology — and data designed for plan B is why the fallback was a same-day change, not a redesign.": "队列位置以分数的形式存着,最初的更新是 read-modify-write:读出分数、内存里算、写回去。并发之下两次更新交错,一次悄悄覆盖了另一次。我把更新重建成包在事务里的原子自增——结果生产环境揭示,我们的 Redis cluster 根本不接受这个事务。好在分数设计从一开始就是分段的——状态、负载、等待时长各占一个数量级——每一次状态变化本来就能表达成一次单独的原子自增,所以我们当天就降级成了纯原子操作。一个修复,要在真实拓扑上活下来才算完——而为 plan B 设计过的数据,正是这次回退只是一个当天的改动、而不是一次重构的原因。", "Two agents, one conversation": "两个客服,一场对话", "Two messages arriving in the same conversation at the same moment each decided a human agent was needed — and two agents got invited into one chat. The fence is a per-room lock: the first caller takes it and performs the invite, everyone else finds it held and walks away, and the lock's time-to-live is aligned to the operation so a crash can't leave the room locked forever. Anything triggered by \"a message arrived\" will eventually be triggered twice in the same millisecond — design for the second caller before it exists.": "同一时刻落进同一个会话的两条消息,各自判断需要转人工——于是两个客服被邀进了同一个聊天。围栏是一把 per-room 锁:第一个调用者拿到锁、执行邀请,其他人发现锁被占就直接走开,锁的存活时间(TTL)对齐操作时长,崩溃也不会把房间永远锁死。任何由「来了一条消息」触发的东西,总有一天会在同一毫秒被触发两次——在第二个调用者出现之前,就为它做设计。", "The model is a dependency you can't trust": "模型是一个不能信任的依赖", "AI answering first means AI failing first. Every model call races a ten-second timer, and on stall, error or timeout the conversation is handed straight to a human — the user always ends up with a person, never with a spinner. The model gets treated like any flaky third-party dependency: timeout, fallback, and never in the critical path without an exit. That guard fired in production more than once, and nobody noticed — which was the point.": "AI 先答,意味着 AI 先挂。每一次模型调用都和一个 10 秒的计时器竞速,一旦卡壳、报错或超时,会话直接交给人——用户最终面对的永远是一个人,而不是一个转圈的加载图标。模型被当成任何一个不稳定的第三方依赖来对待:超时、fallback,没有出口就绝不放进关键路径。这个保护在生产上触发过不止一次,而没人察觉——这正是目的。", "← Previous: Scaling 50k → 400k+ users": "← 上一篇:平台扩容:50k → 400k+ 用户", "Next: Cross-stack mission pipeline →": "下一篇:跨栈任务 pipeline →", "Work — Henry Lee": "工作 — Henry Lee", "work": "工作", "The": "全部", "Seven systems, told honestly — every pattern transfers.": "七个系统,如实讲述——每个模式都能迁移复用。", "The life of a": "一条记录的", "record": "一生", "One record, nine systems. Follow the record:": "一条记录,九个系统。跟着记录走:", "millions/day": "数百万/天", "10M+/day · dual-stream join": "上千万/天 · dual-stream join", "Some of these I built, some I run, some my team owns — but the river is one system, and it has to add up end to end.": "有的我亲手建,有的我负责运行,有的归团队——但这条河是一个整体,而它必须首尾对得上。", "The system that makes sure no transaction is ever processed twice.": "保证任何交易永远不会被错误地处理两次的系统。", "Every financial transaction passes one audited approval workflow —": "平台上每一笔金融交易都要经过同一条带审计的审批 workflow——", "millions of transactions a day": "每天数百万笔交易", ". I rebuilt it on Temporal with idempotency by construction (a retry can only return the existing record) and turned integration into a published SDK: adding a new request type is a": "。我把它重建在 Temporal 上,幂等由构造保证(retry 只可能拿回已存在的那条记录),并把接入做成了对外发布的 SDK:新增一种请求类型,只是一张", "two-minute self-service": "两分钟的自助表单", "form.": "。", "I drove the re-architectures that kept the platform up as daily users climbed to 400k+ — one live single-point at a time.": "我主导了那些 re-architecture,在 日活爬到 400k+ 的过程中撑住平台——一次一个线上单点。", "The member management platform grew from 50k to 400k+ and the old mechanisms broke in production. I replaced them live — atomic ID generation cut over with a": "会员管理平台从 50k 涨到 400k+,旧机制在生产上接连破掉。我在线上把它们逐个换掉——ID 生成切到原子方案,cutover 带", "+1-billion offset": "+10 亿的偏移", ", notification fan-out moved to pub/sub, blocking scans made incremental — inside a weekly release train.": ";通知 fan-out 迁到 pub/sub;阻塞式全量扫描改成增量——全部塞进每周发版的节奏里完成。", "The pilot the whole stack migration was judged on — every pattern I set became the template later services copied.": "整个技术栈迁移就看这个 pilot——我立下的每个模式都成了后续服务照抄的模板。", "AI-assisted support with human takeover, built solo on a stack nobody had shipped to production yet. I bought the messaging base and self-built only the differentiators — a routing queue encoding status, load and wait-time into one sorted-set score, AI-to-human handoff, a mini back-office — grew it to a two-person team, and handed it off clean. Being the pilot meant my patterns became the template every later service copied.": "带人工接管的 AI 客服,一个人在谁都没上过生产的技术栈上从零做起。我买下 messaging 底座,只自建差异化层——一个把状态、负载、等待时长编码进单一 sorted-set 分数的路由队列、AI 转人工的 handoff、一个迷你后台——把团队扩到两人,再干净交接。作为 pilot,我立下的模式成了后续每个服务照抄的模板。", "Case 04": "案例 04", "Four services, three languages, a reward path where a double-pay is real loss — I designed the layer that makes payout happen exactly once, zero legacy changes.": "4 个服务、3 种语言、一条重复发放就是真实损失的发奖路径——我设计了让发放恰好一次的那层,旧系统 0 改动。", "A mission pipeline across four services in three languages, composing the platform's existing engines. My design: the": "一条横跨四个服务、三种语言的任务 pipeline,组合平台现有的引擎。我的设计核心是那层", "exactly-once layer": "exactly-once", "— an atomic claims ledger plus a human-readable idempotency key — correct under both workflow replays and message redeliveries.": "——一张原子的 claims 台账,加一个人类可读的幂等 key——在 workflow replay 和消息重投两种情况下都正确。", "Case 05 — Hand-building the platform's highest-volume data path: over ten million records a day": "案例 05 —— 亲手搭建平台量级最猛的数据路径:每天上千万条记录", "Every balance change a user sees, pulled from 10+ heterogeneous systems most of which my team didn't own — aligned record by record.": "用户看到的每一笔余额变动,拉自 10+ 个异构系统、多数还不归我团队所有——逐条对齐。", "Case 06 — Crypto payment rails: a fintech capability at every transaction boundary": "案例 06 —— 加密货币支付通道:每一个交易边界上的 fintech 能力", "A two-year epic threading fiat↔stablecoin conversion through every transaction boundary — where a precision slip is real loss.": "一个两年期 epic,把法币↔stablecoin 转换织进每一个资金边界——一次精度失误就是真实损失。", "Case 07 — The platform's reporting engine for six years, before there was a business-intelligence team": "案例 07 —— 六年间平台的报表引擎,在 BI 团队出现之前", "Multi-view analytics over million-row, long-window queries — 140+ reporting changes, plus regulatory filings on time.": "百万行、长窗口查询的多视角分析——140+ 次报表变更,外加监管报送按时交付。", "roads not taken": "没有走的路", "Roads not": "没有走的", "taken": "路", "Every architecture I run replaced one I personally operated. Here's what lost, and why.": "我现在跑的每一套架构,都替换掉了一套我亲手维护过的。这里是落选者,和它们输掉的原因。", "Cron and scan, versus durable workflows": "Cron 加扫描,还是 durable workflow", "The old platform ran 22+ cron jobs, one of them re-scanning for stuck approvals every single minute. I maintained that for six years — so when durable workflows arrived, I didn't need a blog post to explain why retries belong in the engine, not in a scanner. What would change my mind: a workload where every task is truly fire-and-forget.": "旧平台跑着 22+ 个 cron job,其中一个每分钟重扫一遍卡住的审批。这套东西我维护了六年——所以 durable workflow 一来,不需要谁写博客来说服我:retry 应该住在引擎里,而不是扫描器里。什么会让我改主意:一个所有任务都真正 fire-and-forget 的场景。", "Tune the database harder, versus add a cache": "把数据库调得更狠,还是加一层缓存", "Redis was not the first answer — months of index work, aggregation rewrites and dead-index deletion came first. The cache earned its place only after the database was already honest. What would change my mind: nothing; the order itself is the principle.": "Redis 不是第一个答案——先来的是几个月的 index 功课、aggregation 重写、删掉死 index。等数据库已经诚实了,缓存才配拿到自己的位置。什么会让我改主意:没有;这个顺序本身就是原则。", "The benchmark that lost, then won": "输掉的 benchmark,后来赢了", "An analytics engine failed our JSON-path queries — 3 to 15 times slower. Instead of accepting the verdict, we flattened the schema and removed the weakness, and the verdict changed. Benchmarks are inputs to architecture, not judges of it.": "一个分析型引擎在我们的 JSON-path 查询上败下阵来——慢 3 到 15 倍。我们没有接受判决,而是把 schema 拍平、移除弱点,判决就变了。Benchmark 是架构的输入,不是它的法官。", "Local models, versus a tiered router": "本地模型,还是分层 tiered router", "At home I wanted local models for everything — free, private, mine. CPU-only inference lost to multi-round tool calling by an order of magnitude, so a tiered router took its place. Losing cleanly beats winning on paper.": "在家里我什么都想用本地模型——免费、私有、属于我自己。CPU-only 推理在多轮 tool calling 上输了一个数量级,于是 tiered router 顶了上来。干脆地输,好过纸面上赢。", "where this happened": "这些都发生在哪", "Where this": "这些都发生在", "happened": "哪", "Dec 2019 – present · Malaysia": "2019 年 12 月 – 至今 · 马来西亚", "A high-concurrency transaction platform": "一个高并发的 高并发交易平台", "A five-person team owning six module domains across two generations of stack — legacy monolith and modern microservices — plus third-party service integrations. Architecture gatekeeper for cross-team requirements. I grow engineers through ownership — three juniors now run an entire production platform themselves. Weekly releases, CI/CD discipline, mentoring as the core of the job.": "一个五人团队,负责横跨两代技术栈的六个模块域——旧的单体和新的微服务——外加第三方服务集成。跨团队需求的架构把关人。我靠 ownership 培养工程师——三个 junior 现在自己撑起一个完整的生产平台。每周发版、CI/CD 纪律,mentoring 是这份工作的核心。", "2,000+ merged pull requests, from full-stack on the legacy platform to pioneering the new stack. Highlights beyond the case studies: hardened withdrawal flows, peer-to-peer order matching (50+ pull requests in two months), session security, and third-party WebSocket integrations with heartbeat keep-alives. The SDK-per-domain pattern I pioneered for the workflow platform has since become the platform standard — a shared SDK layer of 14 packages, consumed by 8 services, built by the platform team on that model.": "2,000+ 个 merge 掉的 PR,从旧平台的全栈一路做到新技术栈的开荒。案例之外的亮点:加固提现流程、用户间订单撮合(两个月 50+ 个 PR)、会话安全,以及带心跳保活的第三方 WebSocket 集成。我为 workflow 平台开创的 SDK-per-domain 模式,如今成了平台标准——平台团队照这个模式建起了 14 个包的共享 SDK 层,8 个服务在用。", "2018 – 2019 · Malaysia": "2018 – 2019 · 马来西亚", "Mobile Engineer": "移动端工程师", "Insurance point-of-sale hybrid app; automated the daily QA deployment.": "保险 POS 混合应用;把每天的 QA 部署自动化了。", "Core (ships daily)": "核心(每天在用)", "TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC / proto-first contracts · MongoDB (aggregation, indexing, Atlas Search) · Redis (data-structure design, cluster) · Temporal · Apache Pulsar · Jest + Testcontainers (real databases, not mocks)": "TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC / proto 先行的契约 · MongoDB(aggregation、索引、Atlas Search)· Redis(数据结构设计、cluster)· Temporal · Apache Pulsar · Jest + Testcontainers(跑真实数据库,不是 mock)", "Working": "熟练", "Java (Flink streaming jobs) · Rust (one full service — Temporal SDK, tonic/prost — pre-production) · Apache Flink (DataStream + SQL, managed) · ClickHouse · Hologres · PostgreSQL · HashiCorp Vault · OpenTelemetry · Grafana · Alibaba Cloud SLS (log forensics) · LangChain / LLM app development": "Java(Flink 流式作业)· Rust(一个完整服务——Temporal SDK、tonic/prost——pre-production)· Apache Flink(DataStream + SQL,托管版)· ClickHouse · Hologres · PostgreSQL · HashiCorp Vault · OpenTelemetry · Grafana · 阿里云 SLS(日志取证)· LangChain / LLM 应用开发", "Familiar": "用过", "Kafka · Node/Express legacy patterns · Socket.io / self-hosted messaging backbones · AngularJS-era stack · Docker · GitHub Actions · Alibaba Cloud (application level)": "Kafka · Node/Express 旧式模式 · Socket.io / 自托管 messaging backbone · AngularJS 时代的技术栈 · Docker · GitHub Actions · 阿里云(应用层)", "Home lab": "家庭实验室", "Python (pandas · FastAPI · Streamlit) · Telegram &amp; WhatsApp bots · Tailscale · WSL2 · Ollama (local LLMs) · vector memory &amp; embeddings · Zeabur": "Python(pandas · FastAPI · Streamlit)· Telegram 与 WhatsApp bot · Tailscale · WSL2 · Ollama(本地 LLM)· 向量记忆与 embeddings · Zeabur", "I build the backend systems a high-concurrency transaction platform runs on —": "我构建一个真实资金平台赖以运转的后端系统 —", "and lead the team that keeps them": "并带领团队让它们", "correct at scale": "在规模下保持正确", "Open to backend team-lead and senior platform roles.": "开放后端 team-lead 与资深平台方向的机会。", "Short, practical lessons from operating production systems.": "来自运维生产系统的简短、实用经验。", "Lead Software Engineer Dec 2025– · Senior Software Engineer 2024–2025 · Software Engineer 2019–2024": "Lead Software Engineer 2025-12 起 · Senior Software Engineer 2024–2025 · Software Engineer 2019–2024", "engineer → senior → lead": "工程师 → senior → lead", "Resume (PDF)": "简历(PDF)"};